Cascading

Selector Specificity
    The type selector has the lowest specificity weight and holds a point value of 0-0-1.
    The class selector has a medium specificity weight and holds a point value of 0-1-0.
    The ID selector has a high specificity weight and holds a point value of 1-0-0.

key selector - The selector farthest to the right, directly before the opening curly bracket
prequalifier - Any selector to the left of the key selector

CSS colors - sRGB - 4 primary ways to represent
    1.  keywords                -   black, silver, gray, white, maroon, red, purple, ...
    2.  hexadecimal notation    -   #ff6600 could also be written as #f60
                                -   0 equals black and f equals white
    3.  RGB                     -   rgb(255, 102, 0)
                                -   rgba(255, 102, 0, 0.5) for transparency
                                -   0 means transparent and 1 means opaque
    4.  HSL values              -   hue, saturation, and lightness
                                -   hsl(0, 100%, 25%)
                                -   hsla(0, 100%, 25%, .25) for transparency
https://kuler.adobe.com/

display - block, inline, inline-block, and none

Box Model
width, height, padding, border, margin
    Inline-level elements cannot have a fixed size, thus the width and height properties are only relevant to non-inline elements
    inline-level elements do not accept vertical margins, top and bottom

margin: 20px;               -   all
margin: 10px 20px;          -   top,bottom right,left
margin: 10px 20px 0 15px;   -   top right bottom left ( clockwise )

Box Sizing
    box-sizing  -  content-box, padding-box, border-box
        content-box -   default ( additive design ) size of an element begins with the width and height properties, and then any padding, border, or margin property values are added on from there
        padding-box -   includes any padding property values within the width and height of an element
        border-box  -   includes any padding or border property values within the width and height of an element

Most common vendor prefixes :
    Mozilla Firefox: -moz-
    Microsoft Internet Explorer: -ms-
    Webkit (Google Chrome and Apple Safari): -webkit-

